    // ── Scratch space ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // CHECKPOINT : ADD RISK PARTNER AND width and strike to the option
    // tokens A, B.  Current price is P_{A/B} = 2.
    // Actor C believes fair value is P*_{A/B} = 3.
    // He wants to benefit from max(P*_{A/B} - P_{A/B}, 0).
    //
    // (1) Long an OTM call with strike P*_{A/B} = 3
    //       call = max(P*_{A/B} - P_{A/B}, 0) - premia
    //
    // (2) Short a put  [He decides on (2)]
    //       put  = max(P_{A/B} - P*_{A/B}, 0) - premia
    //  => -put  = max(P*_{A/B} - P_{A/B}, 0) + premia = call + 2*premia
    //
    // HIs vision on the velocity of such movement is proportional to the
    //  the time, this vol \propto \sqrt(T), How about we map this to a price  
    //  and then to a tick, if we are seing realized volatility of 20 bps annual effective 
    //   we wnat this to be represented on sqrt(vol /T) as sqrtPriceX96 this the "width" is the
    //   mappiung of this to tickSpace
    //  


uint256 constant DEFAULT_OPTION_RATIO = 1;        // optionRatio per leg (7-bit, max 127)
